   "id": "1257e551",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Example: Markov Stability with PyGenStability\n",
    "\n",
    "This example illustrates how to use PyGenStability for multiscale community detection with Markov Stability analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "bb09521e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import scipy.sparse as sp\n",
    "\n",
    "import pygenstability as pgs\n",
    "from pygenstability import plotting\n",
    "from pygenstability.pygenstability import evaluate_NVI\n",
    "\n",
    "from multiscale_example import create_graph"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a7948ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We first create a stochastic block model graph with some planted partitions at different scales."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "220d6e39",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x125897010>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A, coarse_scale_id, middle_scale_id, fine_scale_id = create_graph() \n",
    "\n",
    "# Create nx graph\n",
    "G = nx.from_numpy_array(A)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute spring layout\n",
    "pos_G = nx.layout.spring_layout(G, seed=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot matrix\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "plt.imshow(A, interpolation=\"nearest\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "30d8ad59",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We then run pygenstability with the continuous_combinatoral constructor, which corresponds to using the combinatorial Laplacian matrix in the Markov Stability.\n",
    "The number and range of markov times, or scales can be specified with max_scale, min_scale and n_scales. They are in log scale by default.\n",
    "The number of Louvain evaluations is specified with n_tries argument.\n",
    "\n",
    "Other options are available, see the documentation: https://barahona-research-group.github.io/PyGenStability/"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "98eea89f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "INFO:pygenstability.pygenstability:Precompute constructors...\n",
      "100%|██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 50/50 [00:02<00:00, 17.93it/s]\n",
      "INFO:pygenstability.pygenstability:Optimise stability...\n",
      "100%|██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 50/50 [00:11<00:00,  4.40it/s]\n",
      "INFO:pygenstability.pygenstability:Apply postprocessing...\n",
      "100%|██████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 50/50 [00:05<00:00,  9.56it/s]\n",
      "INFO:pygenstability.pygenstability:Compute ttprimes...\n",
      "INFO:pygenstability.pygenstability:Identify optimal scales...\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# run markov stability and identify optimal scales\n",
    "results = pgs.run(\n",
    "    sp.csgraph.csgraph_from_dense(A),\n",
    "    min_scale=-1.25,\n",
    "    max_scale=0.75,\n",
    "    n_scale=50,\n",
    "    n_tries=20,\n",
    "    constructor=\"continuous_combinatorial\",\n",
    "    n_workers=4\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "00f2e34b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The standard plot to analyse multiscale clustering results in plot_scan, which shows various informations, such as the number of cluster, stability, normalized variation of information (NVI) between Louvain evalutions, and accros scales (NVI(t, t')). Finally, if computed a scale selection algorithm highlights most robust scales."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "1e88c00b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plots results\n",
    "_ = plotting.plot_scan(results, figure_name=None)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8ca92031",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can then plot the optimall partitions determined with the scale selection algorithm."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "53cf4607",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot optimal partitions\n",
    "plotting.plot_optimal_partitions(G, results, show=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b76375ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we compare the selected partitions with the ground-truth planted partitions using the Normalised Variation of Information (NVI) and observe that MS analysis with optimal scale selection recovers the planted multiscale structure of the network."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "4fb830ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# compare MS partitions to ground truth with NVI\n",
    "def _get_NVI(ref_ids):\n",
    "    return [\n",
    "        evaluate_NVI([0, i + 1], [ref_ids] + results[\"community_id\"])\n",
    "        for i in range(len(results[\"scales\"]))\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "NVI_scores_fine = _get_NVI(fine_scale_id)\n",
    "NVI_scores_middle = _get_NVI(middle_scale_id)\n",
    "NVI_scores_coarse = _get_NVI(coarse_scale_id)\n",
    "scales = results[\"scales\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot NVI scores\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(7, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(scales, NVI_scores_fine, label=\"Fine\")\n",
    "ax.plot(scales, NVI_scores_middle, label=\"Middle\")\n",
    "ax.plot(scales, NVI_scores_coarse, label=\"Coarse\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot selected partitions\n",
    "selected_partitions = results[\"selected_partitions\"]\n",
    "ax.axvline(\n",
    "    x=results[\"scales\"][selected_partitions[0]],\n",
    "    ls=\"--\",\n",
    "    color=\"red\",\n",
    "    label=\"Selected Markov scales\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "for i in selected_partitions[1:]:\n",
    "    ax.axvline(x=results[\"scales\"][i], ls=\"--\", color=\"red\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel=r\"$log_{10}(t)$\", ylabel=\"NVI\")\n",
    "plt.axhline(0, c=\"k\", ls=\"--\")\n",
    "ax.legend(loc=3)\n",
    "plt.xscale(\"log\")\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
